                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-1085" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD BEMBOW</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner is my nephew—this is my waistcoat—when I went out I know it was safe—I never permitted him to take it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Can you swear it was not in your coat when you put it on? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I will.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found it on the steps in Church-passage, and put it into my pocket—I went to my uncle's—he was not at home—I picked it up by the railings—I staid ten minutes—I was not aware that it was his.</p>
